title: Honey part VIII up tonight!
body: Hello! Just wanted to let you guys know that I will be FINALLY posting the last part of Honey tonight. I feel so horrible that I’ve made you all wait so long, but I’ve had an insane week and I have just not been feeling motivated, (love that writer’s block) so it’s been very hard for me to work. But, I think I’m finally happy with the ending! Anticipate angst and lots of romance! If you guys want me to write an epilogue or drabbles with the characters, please let me know! Thank you for all of the support, and I’ll see you tonight <3

summary: Namjoon and Jimin - They’re scarily silent when angry You yell out  in frustration when your boyfriend shoots back another...
body:
Namjoon and Jimin - They’re scarily silent when angry

You yell out  in frustration when your boyfriend shoots back another insult instead of carrying on the conversation about the issue you were trying to address. He’s not home enough anymore, and you tried to talk to him about it, but he’d kicked off and started yelling,

“I’m just asking for you to care a little!” You yell, and your boyfriend is about to reply, when his jaw shuts and twitches as his muscles clench up, “Hey,” You provoke, trying to get him to respond, voice quieter now. He’s just stood opposite you, eyes boring into yours. Great, he’s giving you the silent treatment now.

Namjoon

Your eyes plead with Namjoon to say something, but he doesn’t seem to be paying attention. He has that look on his face that you wish you never had to see - Namjoon is usually so soft and kind, to see him put on such a façade hurts. You’re reminded of a concept his group had a few years back that you hated, because of how angry Namjoon looked. You don’t like when he looks this full of rage. Especially when he’s not talking to you, not telling you how he feels. He’s like a book in an entirely different language.

Jimin

“Please, Jimin? Do you have to do this right now? Can’t we just…” You start, but eventually trail off. Jimin’s usually so upbeat and happy, that this is such a stark contrast and it honestly scares you quite a bit. You’ve seen him do this for days before, remaining completely silent as he broods. His jaw is set, and his arms are folded in a way that makes even him seem intimidating. You find yourself clutching for your last thought, but you’re unable to find it. All you can do is feel yourself begin to cry as you watch your boyfriend’s unusually stoic face.

Masterlist
